<h2>
    Best Time of Year to Catch Smallmouth Bass Near Portland
</h2>
<h3>
    Spring Spawn
</h3>
<p>
    From late April through early June, bass move into shallow waters to spawn. This is when they’re aggressive and easy to locate.
</p>
<h3>
    Summer Feeding Frenzy
</h3>
<p>
    Bass become more active and aggressive in the summer months, especially early in the morning and late afternoon.
</p>
<h3>
    Fall Behavior
</h3>
<p>
    In the fall, bass feed heavily before winter, making it another prime time to fish.
</p>
<h2>
    Proven Techniques and Tactics for Catching Smallmouth Bass
</h2>
<h3>
    Topwater Fishing
</h3>
<p>
    Using poppers and frogs early in the morning or late evening is extremely effective, especially in weedy or shallow areas.
</p>
<h3>
    Jigging and Drop Shot
</h3>
<p>
    These finesse techniques work well near rocky ledges and drop-offs where bass often lurk.
</p>
<h3>
    Spinnerbaits and Crankbaits
</h3>
<p>
    Use these during windy or overcast conditions to trigger reaction bites.
</p>
